info: New Lynn became a borough in 1 April 1929. It had previously been a town district and, before that, part of Waitemata County. Henderson became a borough in 1946 and Glen Eden in 1953. Both were also part of Waitemata County. From 1989 all three boroughs, and Waitemata City, which had been formed in 1974 from the west Auckland part of Waitemata County, were amalgamated into Waitakere City.
